NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: A Million Little Fibers
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Towelie writes a book and it gets selected for Oprah’s book club.  It becomes a best seller with everyone getting a lot help for their addictions; until a faction of Oprah's staff leak the truth about the book.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Manbearpig
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: While assisting an ex-Vice President in his quest for attention, the boys get trapped by a cave-in and while searching for a way out, Cartman discovers treasure.  Now he has to figure out how to get out of the cave without the others knowing about it and he can keep it all for himself.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Tsst
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: When Cartman's mom realizes she can't control her son anymore, she gets help from an expert. Cesar Millan, “The Dog Whisperer" takes on the challenge and while he might have what it takes, Eric Cartman's not going down without a fight.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Make Love, Not Warcraft
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: A renegade player threatens the Massively Multiplayer Online game World of Warcraft and the fate of the game lay in the hands of Cartman, Kyle, Stan and Kenny.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Mystery of the Urinal Deuce
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Cartman reveals who masterminded the attacks of 9/11, while Kyle and Stan search for the real truth; meanwhile Mr. Mackey just wants to know who dropped the deuce in the urinal.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Miss Teacher Bangs a Boy
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Cartman, South Park Elementary’s new hallway monitor, takes it personally when he finds out that a teacher has been kissing a student in his jurisdiction.  He helps Kyle stop his little brother’s affair with his “Nice” hot teacher.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Hell on Earth 2006
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Satan is throwing the world's biggest Halloween costume party, and no one is getting in without a blue wrist band. Unfortunately, even Satan can't plan for everything as a religious organization and the antics of the most notorious serial killers of all time might ruin his good time.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Go God Go (1)
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The topic of evolution is introduced to the 4th graders of South Park Elementary and while their teacher is against the theory a change of mind has implications for the future.  And speaking of the future, Cartman is trying to send himself there; to the exact date that the newest video game console, the Nintendo Wii is being released.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Go God Go XII (2)
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Last week, in an attempt to make his wait for the Wii instantaneous, Cartman froze himself. Through a bizarre twist of fate, he woke up 500 years in the future, where there are warring factions, some angry sea otters, and worst of all: No Nintendo Wii! Will Cartman get out of this crazy future? Or will he be doomed to never get his hands on the Wii?

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Stanley's Cup
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Stan becomes coach of a Pee Wee Hockey team and for the benefit of one his players he tries to make them into a team of winners.  Meanwhile his father deals with the memory of Stan’s performance in a Pee Wee hockey game from years earlier, when Stan had the opportunity to score the game winning goal.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: With Apologies to Jesse Jackson
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Randy uses the "N" word on live TV and faces public ridicule for it and Stan tries to understand Token's feelings on the subject. Meanwhile, a little person visits South Park Elementary and Cartman can't stop himself from laughing at him.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Cartman Sucks
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Butters' dad sends him off to special camp to "Pray the Gay Away" when he believes that his son is bi-curious after catching him in a compromising position with Cartman.  Meanwhile, Cartman does his best to retrieve a photo of him in that compromising position before too many people find out about it.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Lice Capades
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: When a breakout of headlice hits South Park Elementary, Mrs. Garrison refuses to say which child brought the plague to the school. So, Cartman takes it upon himself to find out who it is so the kids can make fun of them. Meanwhile, a louse Travis, is desperate to save his fellow lice from imminent destruction from a conscious world.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: The Snuke
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The citizens of South Park are gearing up for the arrival of Hillary Clinton for a big campaign rally. Meanwhile, Cartman suspects that a new Muslim student is involved in a possible terrorist attack. Every minute counts for Cartman as he uses his own interrogation methods on his suspect. But could the plan to target Clinton be just the tip of the iceberg?

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Fantastic Easter Special
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Stan wants to know the real reason kids have to decorate eggs for Easter, and what, if anything eggs and bunnies have to do with Jesus dying for his sins. To get to the bottom of it, Kyle and Stan get wrapped up in a bizarre society that guards a legendary secret.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: D-Yikes!
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Once again Ms. Garrison gets dumped, but this time she decides to take it out on her fourth grade class. When the boys have finally had enough of their teacher's erratic mood swings and excessive homework assignments, they find out that there are people-for-hire that can help out in any situation. Meanwhile, Ms. Garrison is finding life without men has its upsides.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Night of the Living Homeless
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The number of homeless people in South Park is increasing as they eat, sleep, and beg for change across the town. While the adults try to find creative solutions to deal with the homeless, the boys are trying to figure out a way to solve the problem for good

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Le Petit Tourette
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Upon discovering Tourette's syndrome, Cartman becomes mad with power. He finds out he has the ability to say whatever he wants without consequence, so he sets up National TV Coverage to take full advantage of his new found life.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: More Crap
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Stan's dad becomes South Park's home-town hero when the guys down at the local bar see the size of his most recent crap. Randy contacts a society that keeps track of the world record, thinking his masterpiece would definitely be a contender.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Imaginationland
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: When the entire contents of the world's imagination lay open before them, Stan and Kyle step right in. Back in South Park, Cartman swears he's seen a leprechaun.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Imaginationland, Episode II
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Stan and Kyle are being held captive at the Pentagon until they tell the government exactly how they got into Imaginationland. Elsewhere, Cartman will not give up his quest to make Kyle follow through on their bet to suck his balls.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Imaginationland, Episode III
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Inside Imaginationland, Stan and Butters engage in the battle of their lives as they fight the army of evil imaginary forces. Meanwhile, Cartman goes all the way to the Supreme Court to get Kyle to suck his balls.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Guitar Queer-O
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Stan and Kyle become obsessed with Guitar Hero to the point where they're breaking high score records. It doesn't take long for Stan to realize that he could go even further with a different partner. Will the stress of being a rock star get to Stan now that his best friend is no longer by his side?

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: The List
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The girls in the fourth grade class have made a secret list that rates every boy's looks from cutest to ugliest. When the boys steal the list, they are completely unprepared to deal with the results.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Tonsil Trouble
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: After going in for a routine tonsillectomy, a botched transfusion leaves Cartman afflicted with an incurable disease. When he finds no comfort in his friends and family, how far will he go to find a cure?

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Britney's New Look
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: While trying to escape her troubles in the secluded mountains near South Park, Britney Spears has a run-in with the boys. Stan and Kyle get swept up in her celebrity as well as the non-stop feeding frenzy that plagues her wherever she goes. The boys must take Britney to the North Pole when they learn the secret behind what makes her so popular.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Major Boobage
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: In a South Park homage to the 1981 film, “Heavy Metal”, the boys are trying to get Kenny off the latest drug craze that’s captured the junior high and under set.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Canada on Strike
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The head of the World Canadian Bureau leads the country into a long and painful strike and the responsibility of brokering a settlement rests with the boys.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Eek, A Penis!
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: While Ms. Garrison is off trying to find a way to become the man he was always intended to be, Cartman is put in charge of the classroom.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Over Logging
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The citizens of South Park wake up one morning shocked to find the Internet is gone. Upon hearing news that the Internet may remain in California, Randy decides to head out west with the family.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Super Fun Time
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: While the kids are on an educational field trip to a living museum, Cartman makes Butters sneak away from the class to go to the amusement center located next door.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: The China Probrem
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: After watching the intimidating opening ceremonies of the recent Olympic games, Cartman understands that the Chinese are only just days away from invading his homeland. While the rest of the American people are haunted by the memory of a recent tragic event, only Butters will stand with Cartman as he confronts the Chinese.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Breast Cancer Show Ever
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Wendy gets in trouble when she threatens to beat up Cartman after school. No matter how fired up Wendy is, all bets are on Cartman. Everybody knows a girl can't fight a boy and win.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Pandemic
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The boys find a way to make money off an international crisis that requires no talent and very little effort. Cartman convinces the other boys to invite Craig to get in on their latest plan. He knows Craig has just what it takes to make their dream a reality.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Pandemic 2: The Startling
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Giant guinea pigs are attacking cities all over the world. The boys have the key that will save everyone from the onslaught but they're stranded in the Andes Mountains.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: About Last Night...
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: While the country celebrates the outcome of the election, the new President-elect catches everyone off guard when he arrives at the White House prematurely.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Elementary School Musical
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Stan realizes he could lose Wendy if he doesn't get on board with the latest fad to hit South Park Elementary. Cartman would rather kill himself than succumb. But, when Stan, Kyle, Kenny and Cartman all realize that Butters is now more popular than they are, they have no choice but to give in to peer pressure.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: The Ungroundable
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Butters is sure he’s seen a vampire at school but he can’t get anyone to listen to him. Meanwhile, the Goth Kids are angry and frustrated when the other kids can’t tell the difference between a Goth and a Vampire.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: The Ring
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Thinking it's his way into her heart and other body parts, Kenny takes his new girlfriend to a Jonas Brothers concert. His dream of taking their relationship to the next level is crushed when the Jonas Brothers give them purity rings.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: The Coon
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: “The Coon” rises from the trash and takes his place as a lone vigilante who wipes out crime in the town of South Park. A rival superhero appears on the scene in the form of “Mysterion” and challenges the Coon’s place as a “symbol” for the town.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Margaritaville
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Randy steps forward with a solution to fix the desperate financial state everyone finds themselves in. The town gets behind him and everyone starts to live a life that no longer depends on any economy at all. Meanwhile an unlikely savior makes the ultimate sacrifice to solve everyone’s problems.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Eat, Pray, Queef
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Someone played an April Fools joke on the boys and it didn't go over well. Butters is incapacitated, Cartman is furious and the rest of the boys are afraid someone might do it again.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Fishsticks
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Cartman decides to help Jimmy with his comedy routine. Everyone loves the new joke they come up with. The joke starts to take off and it even hits all the late night talk shows. The boys are thrilled with how popular it’s become until somebody tries to take all the credit.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Pinewood Derby
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Randy is determined that Stan will win this year's Pinewood Derby. He comes up with a plan that will assure Stan a first place trophy.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Fatbeard
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Butters and a small group of recruits join Cartman in his dream of living on skull island. Cartman promises that paradise awaits if they can just get to Somalia.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Dead Celebrities
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Powerful forces are tormenting Ike. He's freaked out and the stress could kill him. Kyle and the boys are doing everything they can to save him but the poltergeists won't leave Ike alone.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Butters' Bottom Bitch
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Butters has made it all the way to the 4th grade without ever kissing a girl. All of his friends have been teasing him mercilessly. Butters is determined to catch up with the rest of the boys in his class. Meanwhile, one overly dedicated cop wages war on prostitution in South Park.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: W.T.F.
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The boys have found their new calling in life and they hurry to sign up for the wrestling club. They soon find out the kind of wrestling they teach at school is not the same thing they saw at the WWE.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Whale Whores
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Stan and his family are spending his birthday at the Denver Aquarium where they will get to swim with the dolphins. Things turn bloody when the Japanese attack, kill all the dolphins and ruin Stan’s big day. There seems to be no end to the senseless killing. Stan takes on the cause to save the dolphins from the Japanese.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: The F Word
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Everyone agrees they've had enough of the loud and obnoxious bikers that have arrived in South Park. The boys are taking on the Harley Riders. They thrown down the F word and the game is on.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Dances With Smurfs
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Eric Cartman seizes the opportunity to become the voice of change at the school when he takes over the morning announcements. His target is South Park Elementary’s Student Body President, Wendy Testaburger. Cartman is asking the tough questions and gaining followers.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Pee
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Things at the water park are not what they seem. The boys' fun filled day is about to turn deadly. Events are in play at Splash Town that signal the end of the world is upon us. Cartman tries to warn everyone but no one will listen. Disaster is about to strike and the boys are in a race to survive.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Sexual Healing
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The nation's top scientists come together to put a stop to the recent phenomenon of rich, successful men who suddenly want to have sex with many, many women. After extensive testing, some of the fourth grade boys in South Park Elementary are diagnosed as sex addicts.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: The Tale of Scrotie McBoogerballs
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The boys are given a controversial book to read in school that both excites and inspires them to write one of their own. When the boys discover that Stan's mom has found their masterpiece, their new motivation is how they can stay out of trouble.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Medicinal Fried Chicken
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: State Law in Colorado says it's legal to smoke pot if you have a physician's reference. Randy is the first-in-line to buy some but he's turned away because there's absolutely nothing wrong with him. Randy is desperate to get a medical excuse to smoke some weed but meanwhile, Cartman will do anything to get his beloved fried chicken restaurant back.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: You Have 0 Friends
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Kyle "friended" the wrong person and now all of his old friends are deserting him. His situation is desperate. Kyle looks for help from the one person who has always been there for him.

While on a school field trip, Stan accidentally insults Tom Cruise and sets off a chain reaction. 200 previously ridiculed celebrities stand strong in a class action lawsuit against the town of South Park.
Angry celebrities, violent ginger kids and Mecha Streisand are about to destroy South Park and all anyone wants to know is, “Who is Eric Cartman’s father?”

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Crippled Summer
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Competition is the name of the game this summer. There is no time for Jimmy and his friends to slack off. They're working to be this year's champions at summer camp. Jimmy suits up and prepares to shred in the annual surfing contest.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Poor and Stupid
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Cartman wants to race with the pros and he's ready to do whatever it takes to make it happen. He's afraid that no matter how hard he tries, he'll never reach the level of the other NASCAR drivers. Working with Butters as his pit boss, Cartman pulls out all the stops to compete in the race of his life.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: It's a Jersey Thing
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: New Jersey is rapidly taking over the nation one state at a time and their next stop is South Park.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Insheeption
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: When Stan is sent to the school counselor because he's holding on to an obscene number of useless possessions, he realizes that Mr. Mackey has a hoarding disorder too.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Coon 2: Hindsight
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The Coon now leads an entire team of crime-fighters. They are ready to take their place among the worlds most admired and beloved super heroes. But much to the Coons dismay, someone else keeps beating them to the punch. The nation looks to another hero to get them through the BP disaster and dissention develops within the ranks of Coon and friends.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Mysterion Rises
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Led by Mysterion, Coon and Friends are working together to help the people in the Gulf who are at the mercy of the dark lord, Cthulhu. The Coon, scorned by his fellow super heroes and now working alone, is out for revenge.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Coon vs. Coon & Friends
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The Coon shows himself to be even more evil than the dark lord, Cthulhu, as he punishes his former partners in Coon & Friends. Kenny McCormick, is wrestling with the weight of his own super power through his alter-ego, Mysterion. Will Coon and Friends save the day? Will Mysterion ever come to terms with his ability to defy death? All this as the nation waits and wonders: Where is Captain Hindsight?

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Crème Fraiche
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Stan's life is a shambles both at home and in school. Randy's obsession with the Food Network Is changing everything. It even forces Sharon to explore a new interest of her own.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: HUMANCENTiPAD
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Kyle is intimately involved in the development of a revolutionary new product that is about to be launched by Apple. Meanwhile, Cartman doesn't even have a regular iPad and blames his mother.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Funnybot
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: At the school's first annual Comedy Awards, Jimmy announces that the Germans are the least funny people in the world. Germany is highly insulted. They vow that retaliation toward the kids at South Park Elementary will be swift and brutal.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Royal Pudding
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The Prince of Canada is about to take a Princess and Ike is obsessed with the Royal Wedding.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: T.M.I.
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Cartman is furious when he believes that the school has posted their penis sizes on the bulletin board. He throws an absolute fit; takes matters into his own hands and once again finds himself in the principal's office. This time he gets sent to anger management therapy.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Crack Baby Athletic Association
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview:
Cartman has a new protege. He's found someone who is smart, ambitious and willing to look the other way in order to get to the top.

Kyle is brought in on the ground floor of Cartman's latest business venture, the Crack Baby Athletic Adventure.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: City Sushi
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Butters is diagnosed with multiple personality disorder. Meanwhile, the owner of City Wok is angered when a competing Asian restaurant opens next door.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: You're Getting Old
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: After Stan celebrates his 10th birthday, he begins to see everything differently. The other boys think he's become a major buzzkill and start to avoid hanging out with him. When Stan and Kyle have a major blow up, the very fabric of South Park begins to unravel.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Ass Burgers
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Cartman finds a unique way of coping with Asperger's Syndrome. Even Kyle and Kenny are on board. Meanwhile, Stan can't seem to get his life back to normal no matter what he tries. Will anything ever be the same in South Park again?

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: The Last of the Meheecans
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: What begins as an innocent game between the boys turns serious when Cartman joins the U.S. Border Patrol. Not surprisingly, Cartman turns out to be really good at stopping Mexicans.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Bass to Mouth
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The students of South Park Elementary are the victims of a new gossip website. An elusive hacker has somehow gained access into the student's confidential phone calls and e-mails and is posting all their juicy stories. The boys are shocked when they discover the identity of the hacker.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Broadway Bro Down
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Sharon is thrilled that Randy is making an effort to do more things that she enjoys. But, after he takes her to see a hit musical in Denver, Randy becomes Broadway’s biggest fan. Sharon is whisked away to New York and treated to every musical on the Great White Way.
The kids at South Park Elementary are being punished for Cartman's failings in the physical education department. What will Cartman do when they all gang up on him?

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: A History Channel Thanksgiving
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: After watching a Thanksgiving special on The History Channel, the boys believe that aliens were involved in the original feast. But, questions remain... was the first Thanksgiving haunted? Is alien technology responsible for stuffing? The truth could change Thanksgiving for everyone.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: The Poor Kid
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: With their parents in jail, Kenny and his brother and sister find themselves in the foster care system. Cartman is sincerely disturbed when Kenny is taken away. He doesn't know who to rip on for being the poorest kid in school anymore.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Reverse Cowgirl
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: One of the boys had been told time and time again about leaving the toilet seat up after he goes to the bathroom, but he didn't listen. His actions have consequences and ultimately result in an unimaginable catastrophe.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Cash for Gold
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Cartman launches a gemstones network show and creates a very lucrative business. Stan searches for the real value of a piece of jewelry that was a gift from his Grandpa. Meanwhile, Cartmans lucrative new business preys upon an extremely vulnerable clientele.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Faith Hilling
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Mankind's evolution begins to accelerate at a rapid and disturbing pace. Concurrently, another species on the planet is exhibiting the same drastic development. Eventually the two species will battle to the death and "Faith Hilling" may be humanity's only hope.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Jewpacabra
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: South Park's big Easter egg hunt is in jeopardy when there are rumors of a dangerous beast lurking in the woods nearby. Cartman tries to warn everyone that their lives are at risk if they participate in the egg hunt. No one believes him until he produces video evidence of the mystery being.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Butterballs
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Stan wants to raise awareness about the dangers of bullying by shooting a big dance video, while Butters falls victim to an unlikely bully.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: I Should Have Never Gone Ziplining
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.SortName: 016 - 0006 - I Should Have Never Gone Ziplining
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The boys try zip-lining in the Colorado mountains on the last day of spring break, but their adventure takes a dangerous, life-threatening turn.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Cartman Finds Love
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: There's a new girl in school and everyone wants to know who she has a crush on. Cartman is especially excited. He's discovered something inside himself that he never knew he had. Now, to make sure nobody gets in the way of true love, it's time for Cartman to finally let someone know exactly how he feels.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Sarcastaball
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Randy's campaign to prevent head injuries in football radically changes the way the game is played, but the new rules become a national sensation and even make a South Park student a star athlete.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Raising the Bar
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Cartman owns up to being fat and decides that driving around on a scooter is his right. Kyle sees that Cartman isn't the only one who finds no shame in his unhealthy lifestyle. Meanwhile, Cartman discovers he has a rival in America’s Sweetheart, Honey Boo Boo.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Insecurity
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The man who visits all the homes in South Park every day is under suspicion. Cartman takes matters into his own hands and signs up for a home security system.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Going Native
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: It is time for Butters to begin a journey where he will follow in the path of his Hawaiian ancestors.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: A Nightmare on FaceTime
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The boys plans to go as the Avengers for Halloween go awry when Randy can’t go at the last minute and Stan has to help his father with a new business venture.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: A Scause for Applause
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Rocked by the recent news of drug use by a beloved icon, the world is left feeling lost and betrayed. The boys, join with the rest of the nation, and remove their yellow wristbands. Everyone is on board, except for Stan, who just can’t seem to cut off his bracelet.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Obama Wins!
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Eric Cartman is hiding something in his bedroom that could change the entire outcome of the Presidential election.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Let Go, Let Gov
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: When Cartman manages to get himself behind the doors of the NSA, he doesn’t like what he finds in his personal file. He thinks it’s time he told everyone the truth. Meanwhile, Butters finds someone new to listen to his prayers.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Informative Murder Porn
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The boys use the game of MINECRAFT as a distraction to keep their parents from hurting each other.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: World War Zimmerman
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Cartman is deeply disturbed by a single person who he sees as a threat to all humanity. He races around the country to put an end to Patient Zero, the ticking time bomb that is Token.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Goth Kids 3: Dawn of the Posers
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.SortName: 017 - 0004 - Goth Kids 3: Dawn of the Posers
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: One of the Goth kids has been sent to a camp for troubled children. When she returns, her friends find her changed in a disturbing way. With their very existence threatened, the Goths have to do something drastic. They are forced to ask the Vamp kids for help.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Taming Strange
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: When Ike hits puberty, he and Kyle start to grow apart. To save their relationship, Kyle takes Ike to see a live performance of Yo Gabba Gabba.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Ginger Cow
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Cartman's latest prank has brought about the necessary spiritual conditions for world peace. Religious leaders descend upon South Park to witness a Biblical prophecy that has been fulfilled. Cartman and Kyle are the only two at odds as the world embarks upon a thousand years of peace and harmony.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Black Friday
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Anticipation for the biggest shopping day of the year is building. The dark days of winter are coming and that can only mean one thing: the fight to be the first in the mall on Black Friday has begun. The boys prepare to battle the crowds the day after Thanksgiving to get the best deal on the new gaming systems.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: A Song of Ass and Fire
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.SortName: 017 - 0008 - A Song of Ass and Fire
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Hordes of souless shoppers approach the mall in anticipation of the Black Friday sales. The kids prepare for an epic battle where one faction's favorite gaming device will come out on top. Will Stan and Kyle's friendship survive Black Friday?

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Titties and Dragons
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The doors to the mall will finally open for the biggest Black Friday sale in history. The boys are divided over which gaming device to buy and a bloody battle will determine whether Xbox or Sony will be the winner.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: The Hobbit
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: When Wendy tries to prove a point about how much pressure little girls feel to look like celebrities, it gets her in trouble with everyone at school, and gets Clyde a new girlfriend.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Go Fund Yourself
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: After Cartman and the boys name their new company, The Washington Redskins, they just sit back and watch the funding roll in. The head coach of the Washington Redskins football team demands that they change the name but Cartman digs in his heels. The Washington Redskins may never mean the same thing ever again.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Gluten Free Ebola
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Mr. Mackey is now gluten free and everyone is annoyed when he won’t quit preaching about how great he feels. But, after witnessing a disturbing demonstration of what happens to your body when you do eat gluten, South Park becomes the first town in America to go gluten free.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: The Cissy
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Stan is searching for answers about how a person who he’s always known to be one thing could suddenly identify with another. In the meantime, the pressure of holding on to a giant secret is starting to get to Randy.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Handicar
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Timmy’s idea to raise money for the summer camp has everyone in South Park trying out the latest trend in transportation. Timmy’s success makes him a lot of enemies and a bloodbath of epic proportions is on the horizon.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: The Magic Bush
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: A scandalous invasion of privacy has everyone in South Park on edge when graphic video from an unknown drone is uploaded on the internet. Cartman and Butters get their hands on a drone and can't resist the urge to take it for a spin around the neighborhood.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Freemium Isn't Free
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The kids in “South Park” are playing the new Terrance and Phillip mobile game. Stan is addicted to the latest app to hit the market. Meanwhile, Terrance and Phillip aren’t feeling so good about the fortune they’re making on their new mobile game.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Grounded Vindaloop
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Butters is convinced that he’s living in a virtual reality. When he suddenly goes rogue and wreaks havoc at home and all over South Park, everyone struggles to figure out what’s real.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Cock Magic
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Kenny excels at playing the game, Magic: The Gathering. He has the boys’ full attention until a new, hard-core activity gets in the way. When Wendy tries to get Stan to pay attention to what she’s doing, she realizes that what he does with his guy friends always comes first.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: #REHASH
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: After Ike refuses to play a new game with Kyle, Kyle thinks the new generation of kids is terrible. Cartman becomes part of this new generation. Meanwhile Randy has drama going on with the music industry.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: #HappyHolograms
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview:
Kyle plans a holiday special for TV in hopes of bringing families together again with help from some of the biggest names in entertainment.

Meanwhile, Cartmaaan Bra is still trending as holograms continue to run rampant in South Park.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Stunning and Brave
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: There is a new principal at the helm of South Park Elementary. He forces the boys to confront the damage they’ve done through their history of racism and unconscious bias. It is the most stunning and brave South Park ever.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Where My Country Gone?
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Mr Garrison is fed up with undocumented immigrants, and proposes building a wall to keep them out.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: The City Part of Town
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: As the town is gentrifying around him, Kenny attempts to climb out of the cycle of poverty by taking a job at City Wok.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: You're Not Yelping
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: There’s a new kid in school and his parents have opened a restaurant in the recently gentrified part of town. Cartman now considers himself the top on-line restaurant reviewer in South Park.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Safe Space
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Cartman is the latest victim of body shaming on Twitter. Randy has to deal with uncomfortable confrontations every time he shops at the new Whole Foods. He feels exposed at every turn and it’s ruining his Whole Foods experience. Randy and Cartman are both seeking a safe space.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Tweek x Craig

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: PC Principal disappears with two of the 4th grade students.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: PC Principal Final Justice
NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The gentrification of South Park is pricing Randy right out of town. Meanwhile, Kyle’s distrust of Stan has broken their friendship and thrown Kyle into a dangerous alliance.

At the cafeteria, Stan is suggesting that they need to stop Skankhunt42 immediately.

Gerald faces ruin if his complete history of internet activity becomes public. Memberberries are afraid for their lives and Cartman starts to realize the future is in jeopardy.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: PC Principal tries one more time to make peace between the boys and the girls. Meanwhile Gerald comes face-to-face with the Troll Hunter.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: The President-elect has some unfinished business with his hometown, and Gerald tries anything to escape the Troll Hunter’s revenge. Meanwhile, Cartman and Heidi make their way to SpaceX to try to get on the first rocket leaving for Mars.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Overview: Stan and Kyle run away with Ike, Cartmans' trip to mars lands him on death row, Mr. Garrison and Randy help the trolls destroy a country.

NowPlayingQueueFullItems.Name: Franchise Prequel
